    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Kyle Tucker** (73.02) and **Jackson Merrill** (70.91) serving as our primary anchors. **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a high-efficiency matchup against Rea, where his strong xwOBA of .372 and the SP\u2019s manageable 4.36 xERA project a high ceiling. Similarly, **Jackson Merrill** is a locked-in start, bolstered by a significant 13% platoon edge and a favorable slot in the three-hole against Gallen. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (67.40) rounds out our elite tier; despite facing a lefty in Cantillo, he maintains a high-floor profile thanks to a strong 3-hole placement and superior underlying metrics.\n\nThe decision to bench **Coby Mayo** (46.33) was the most difficult call of the morning. While **Coby Mayo** enjoys a significant park factor boost, the combination of a difficult matchup against Crochet\u2019s 2.86 xERA and a lower-than-optimal batting order placement kept his efficiency just shy of the active roster. We are exercising caution with **Gunnar Henderson** (52.11) and **Drake Baldwin** (46.14) due to their exposure to Crochet and Wheeler, respectively; while **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 16% park adjustment, his score is suppressed by the elite skill set of the opposing starter.\n\nRisk management remains paramount, particularly regarding our SB-focused assets. **Heliot Ramos** (45.93) and **Andy Pages** (57.11) remain active due to our strategic weighting on speed, despite the unfavorable SP profiles they face today. We are monitoring the status of **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, who remains benched for this lineup iteration as we prioritize stability in the middle infield slots. All starters should be monitored for late-breaking weather patterns, as the matchups against Wheeler and Crochet present the highest probability for a sub-optimal outcome if conditions deteriorate.",
